Only one of the 140 chemicals on EPAA?s regulated substance list is stored at HCMUD #170 above the threshold.  This is the compressed liquid chlorine used in the disinfection process.  The maximum amount of chlorine contained onsite at any given time is 4,000 pounds.  This is stored in two one-ton cylinders.  The cylinders are located in the central part of the facility.  The threshold quantity for chlorine is 2,500 pounds.
SWWC has implemented safety precautions to prevent and mitigate a chlorine release.  These include maintenance, training, and inspection procedures, as well as an Emergency Action Plan.
HCMUD #170 and SWWC are committed to:
A?Preventing accidents;
A?Training employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;
A?Providing leadership to the community with respect to emergency preparedness;
A?Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with facility operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents; and
A?Being a good corporate citizen of Harris County

With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan provides information about the HCMUD #170 and SWWCA?s management of the risk associated with the chlorine disinfection process, but more importantly stresses the commitment to ensuring a safe operation for employees, visitors, and community.
